Pre-Game Insights: Wales is seeking another slice of playoff glory against Finland in their Euro 2024 qualifying playoff Path A semi-final.
Wales has a strong recent record with a four-match unbeaten run in their Euro 2024 qualifying Group D campaign.
Finland has shown resilience in their qualifying campaign, finishing third in Group H with 18 points.
Wales has only been beaten once in their last 15 European Championship qualifying matches on home turf.
Finland has not won any of their last four matches against Wales, with a draw in their most recent encounter.
Wales has key players like Harry Wilson, Brennan Johnson, and Kieffer Moore in good form.
Finland's Teemu Pukki is close to 40 goals for his country and will be a key threat.
Wales boss Rob Page has dealt with several defensive injuries, but Aaron Ramsey is a surprise inclusion.
Finland's lineup includes experienced players like Glen Kamara and Lukas Hradecky in goal.
The match is expected to be a close contest, with Wales predicted to win 2-0.
